==Old Coast Road==
While much of Old Coast Road was renamed Forrest Highway in 2014, bypassed sections of the former Perth Bunbury Highway near Mandurah and Australind have retained the name Old Coast Road,<ref name="SOD appendices" /> and have significance as part of numbered [[Route number#Australia|road routes]].

===Mandurah <U+2013> Lake Clifton===
{{Infobox road small
|country=AUS
|name=Old Coast Road
|location=[[Mandurah, Western Australia|Mandurah]] <U+2013> [[Lake Clifton, Western Australia|Lake Clifton]]
|length_km=44.3
|length_ref=<ref name="gmaps OCR Mandurah" />
|route={{AUshield|R|1|size=x18px}} [[List of road routes in Western Australia#R1|National Route&nbsp;1]]
}}
Old Coast Road starts at the intersection of Mandurah Terrace and Pinjarra Road in Mandurah. It crosses the Mandurah estuary into [[Halls Head, Western Australia|Halls Head]] via the {{convert|184|m|ft|adj=mid|-long}} Mandurah Bridge.<ref name=RIMS /><ref>{{cite web |author1=City of Mandurah |title=Mandurah Bridge |url=http://inherit.stateheritage.wa.gov.au/Public/Inventory/Details/d41b6a5b-8cc9-4505-8271-614f69e15333 |publisher=State Heritage Office, Government of Western Australia |accessdate=4 August 2014 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20140804071750/http://inherit.stateheritage.wa.gov.au/Public/Inventory/Details/d41b6a5b-8cc9-4505-8271-614f69e15333 |archivedate=4 August 2014 |deadurl=no |date=11 May 2012}} {{cite archives |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6VcDcU33h |archivedate=16 January 2015}}</ref> The road heads south-west as a [[two-lane road]] serving the canal estate in eastern Halls Head. After {{convert|1.7|km}} Old Coast Road intersects Mandurah Road at a T&nbsp;junction. Mandurah Road and Old Coast Road south-westbound form a continuous dual carriageway, and from here Old Coast Road is part of [[Highway 1 (Western Australia)|National Route&nbsp;1]]. The road then proceeds through Mandurah's southern suburbs of [[Falcon, Western Australia|Falcon]] and [[Wannanup, Western Australia|Wannanup]] for {{convert|8.7|km}} before bridging the [[Dawesville Channel]]. After {{convert|1.3|km}}, Old Coast Road turns south to run through eastern Dawesville as a single carriageway; about {{convert|500|m|mi}} to the west the dual carriageway also travels south as Dawesville Bypass. The two routes meet again after {{convert|spell=in|3+1/2|km}}. Old Coast Road is briefly a dual carriageway for {{convert|700|m|mi}} before reducing to a {{convert|28|km|mi|adj=mid|-long}} two-lane road through [[Bouvard, Western Australia|Bouvard]], [[Herron, Western Australia|Herron]] and Lake Clifton. The road terminates at a T junction with Forrest Highway.<ref name="gmaps OCR Mandurah">{{Google maps |url=https://www.google.com.au/maps/dir/-32.5348815,115.718835/-32.5364795,115.7150321/-32.5493835,115.7061523/-32.604693,115.6413619/-32.6073934,115.6392387/-32.6183275,115.6361199/-32.6473328,115.6392623/-32.6529141,115.6430436/-32.8843426,115.7130737/@-32.6866699,115.6774774,11z/am=t/data=!4m21!4m20!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m10!3m4!1m2!1d115.6394446!2d-32.6260709!3s0x2a2d87c2a0760523:0x1304f0b525f062d0!3m4!1m2!1d115.6387472!2d-32.6387162!3s0x2a2d88755152d74f:0xc1d6ff68449b0346!1m0!1m0!1m0!3e0?hl=en |accessdate=3 August 2014 |title=Old Coast Road <U+2013> Mandurah to Lake Clifton |link=no}}</ref>

===Leschenault <U+2013> Pelican Point===
{{Infobox road small
|header_type=historic
|country=AUS
|name=Old Coast Road
|location=[[Leschenault, Western Australia|Leschenault]] <U+2013> [[Pelican Point, Western Australia|Pelican Point]]
|length_km=11.7
|length_ref=<ref name="gmaps OCR Australind" />
|route={{AUshield|T|260|size=x18px}} [[List of road routes in Western Australia#260|Tourist Drive&nbsp;260]]
}}
While Forrest Highway bypasses Australind, there is a turn off for Old Coast Road and Tourist Drive&nbsp;260<ref>{{cite web |author1=Collie Visitor Centre |title=Discover the Collie River Valley |url=http://collie.wa.gov.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/discover_collie_tour1.pdf |publisher=Shire of Collie |accessdate=3 August 2014 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20140226031402/http://collie.wa.gov.au/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/discover_collie_tour1.pdf |archivedate=26 February 2014 |deadurl=no |format=PDF}} {{cite archives |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6VcDkHQ3z#.pdf |archivedate=16 January 2015}}</ref> at Leschenault. The road heads south through the residential suburb for {{convert|spell=in|3+1/2|km}} before going through a {{convert|1.4|km|mi|adj=mid|-long}} reverse curve. Now at the eastern edge of the Leschenault Inlet, Old Coast Road enters [[Australind, Western Australia|Australind]] and travels along the shoreline for {{convert|spell=in|9+1/2|km}}. The road crosses the Collie River, and {{convert|600|m|mi}} later there is a roundabout with Estuary Drive and Hamilton Road. The tourist drive follows Estuary Drive to Bunbury, while Old Coast Road continues south for {{convert|1.4|km}} to rejoin Forrest Highway at the south-eastern edge of [[Pelican Point, Western Australia|Pelican Point]].<ref name="gmaps OCR Australind">{{Google maps |url=https://www.google.com.au/maps/dir/-33.2316229,115.7284671/-33.2621505,115.7253408/-33.2711534,115.7153504/-33.3087193,115.6980612/-33.3097395,115.6971733/-33.3148389,115.6951257/-33.3272561,115.6969717/@-33.267971,115.7117844,12z/am=t/data=!4m9!4m8!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!3e0?hl=en |accessdate=3 August 2014 |title=Old Coast Road <U+2013> Leschenault to Glen Iris |link=no}}</ref>

